practitioner.about:
Dr. Ahmed AS El-Hakeem is a Consultant Surgeon in the Department of General and Laparoscopic Surgery at the Sharjah branch of Medcare Hospital. He completed MBBS from the University of Gezira in Sudan and a Diploma in Laparoscopic Surgery from the European Institute of Telesurgery, Strasbourg, France. He obtained specialized training in General surgery in Ireland.      

He is a member of British Medical Association, a Fellow of the Royal College of Surgeons in Ireland (FRCS), an accredited ALS Provider from Resuscitation Council (UK), a member of the European Association of Endoscopic Surgeons (EAES), a member of the Society of Laparoscopic & Robotic Surgeons and a member of the European Institute of Telesurgery (EITS).

Dr.Ahmed trained and practised as a  General surgery in Connolly Hospital, an affiliate of the Royal College of Surgeons, Ireland. He attained the Fellowship of the Royal College of Surgeons in Ireland. He practiced as Consultant General and laparoscopic Surgeon in the United Kingdom & Ireland. Ad subsequently a surgical Lecturer in RCSI (Ireland). After moving to the UAE he served as Adjunct Clinical Assistant Professor at the University of Sharjah and as Consultant General & Laparoscopic Surgeon in NMC Royal Hospital Sharjah, UAE. He is committed to continuous learning and skill improvement, ensuring his patients consistently receive the highest standard of care.

Dr. Ahmad is expertise covers gastrointestinal endoscopy, laparoscopic cholecystectomy, appendectomy and the intricate realm of hernia repairs, including the complexities of laparoscopic procedures. He has successfully managed anal/ rectal conditions like anal fistula and anal fissure repair, employing advanced methods such as THD for haemorrhoids, breast surgery including lumpectomy and mastectomy for both benign and malignant breast cysts and thyroid surgery. He has proficiency in pilonidal cyst excision, surgical drainage, wound debridement including diabetic foot ulcer, lymph node biopsy and skin lesion removal. He conducts diagnostic procedures using state-of-the-art methods such as colonoscopy, laparoscopy, biopsies, and fine needle aspirations. He addresses skin and soft tissue tumours, along with general wound care, including diabetic foot ulcers. He believes in providing his patients with the highest standard of care, marked by expertise, compassion, and an unyielding commitment to their health.

He speaks both Arabic and English.

locations.name: Medcare Hospital Sharjah
locations.about:
MedCare Multi Specialty Hospital Sharjah is a part of MedCare Network, a premium healthcare network. The hospital is a venture of Aster DM Healthcare, a global healthcare group with 317 medical establishments in 9 countries, including the GCC, India, and Africa. MedCare Multi Specialty Hospital is committed to providing high quality and personalized medical care for every patient.

MedCare has a premium healthcare network consisting of 4 multispeciality hospitals, 4 speciality centres, 9 medical centres, and over 300 experienced doctors. What makes MedCare different is the exceptional multi-cultural, multi-lingual team of doctors and physicians, who have received extensive training from medical institutes in the United States, United Kingdom, Greece, Australia, France, India, Africa, and the Middle East. The doctors and staffs listen to the patients to really understand their problems and then recommend the best step to take. MedCare’s team of doctors provide optimal guideline-based treatment to patients, with the support of a team of trained nurses, dieticians, rehabilitation therapists, and technologists.

MedCare Multi Specialty Hospital in Sharjah has a mission to develop a leading healthcare system that promotes and supports the highest standards in preventive, curative, and rehabilitative healthcare, regionally and internationally. All 4 MedCare multispecialty hospitals are accredited by the Joint Commission International, which is considered as the gold standard in healthcare around the globe.

Apart from many departments with various services, MedCare Multi Specialty Hospital also offers health packages for maternity, health checkup, and medical tourism. All the departments are led by experts in hospital quality management.

MedCare Multi Specialty Hospital in Sharjah is driven by 6 main values: Integrity, Passion, Respect, Excellence, Compassion, and Unity.

Ideal for patients of every age seeking precise diagnoses and prompt treatment across various specialties. At the helm of Medcare Medical Centre Al Zahia is a team of multicultural, multilingual doctors, complemented by exceptionally-trained and experienced nurses and medical staff. The centre takes pride in its extensive array of stateof-the-art equipment, empowering its highly skilled medical team to deliver a premium level of care to all patients. Experience the warmth of family-centric care delivered by our highly talented medical and non-medical staff.
